    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]<strong> </span>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop everything finely!</p><p>Grind to a fine paste, then add your<strong> mayo </strong>with a squeeze of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon juice</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and stir it all together – this is your <strong>coriander chutney</strong></p>",
